b-6">Invisalign</h1><p class="text-white/70 leading-8 text-lg max-w-3xl mb-8">Clear aligners can straighten crowded, spaced, or shifted teeth without brackets and wires. Elm Ridge plans Invisalign around both smile appearance and long-term bite health.</p><a href="/#contact" class="inline-block bg-teal px-8 py-4 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest font-semibold">Request an Invisalign Consultation</a></div></section><section class="py-16 bg-white"><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-7 leading-8 text-charcoal/70"><p>Invisalign is often thought of as cosmetic treatment, but alignment is also functional. Teeth that fit together better can be easier to clean, can look more balanced, and may reduce uneven stress on restorations. For patients considering whitening, bonding, veneers, crowns, or implants, moving teeth first can sometimes make cosmetic treatment more conservative.</p><h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-charcoal">Who Invisalign Can Help</h2><p>Invisalign may be appropriate for mild to moderate crowding, spacing, rotated teeth, relapse after braces, and selected bite concerns. During your visit, we evaluate gum health, tooth position, bite forces, wear patterns, and your cosmetic goals before recommending treatment.</p><h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-charcoal">What Treatment Is Like</h2><p>Patients wear a series of clear aligners that gently move teeth over time. Aligners must be worn consistently to work well. You remove them for eating, drinking anything besides water, brushing, and flossing. We monitor progress and make adjustments when needed.</p><h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-charcoal">Invisalign Before Cosmetic Dentistry</h2><p>Some patients want veneers or bonding because teeth look uneven, but the real issue is tooth position. Invisalign can improve the foundation before cosmetic work, which may reduce how much tooth structure needs to be changed. This is especially helpful for patients who want natural-looking results.</p><h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-charcoal">Invisalign FAQ</h2><div class="space-y-4"><details class="bg-stone border border-teal-light p-6"><summary class="font-semibold">Is Invisalign painful?</summary><p class="mt-3">Most patients feel pressure or soreness when switching aligners. That usually improves as teeth adapt.</p></details><details class="bg-stone border border-teal-light p-6"><summary class="font-semibold">How long does Invisalign take?</summary><p class="mt-3">Timing depends on the amount of movement needed and how consistently aligners are worn.</p></details><details class="bg-stone border border-teal-light p-6"><summary class="font-semibold">Can adults get Invisalign?</summary><p class="mt-3">Yes. Many adults choose Invisalign because it is discreet and can fit professional and family life.</p></details></div></div></section><section class="py-16 bg-charcoal text-white text-center"><h2 class="font-display text-4xl mb-4">Want to see if clear aligners fit your goals?</h2><a href="/#contact" class="inline-block bg-teal px-8 py-4 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest font-semibold">Request an Appointment</a></section><section class="py-12 bg-white"><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 border border-teal-light bg-stone p-7"><h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-charcoal mb-3">Invisalign Insurance</h2><p class="text-charcoal/65 leading-7 mb-5">Learn how orthodontic benefits, lifetime maximums, and adult coverage may apply to Invisalign.</p><a href="/insurance/invisalign" class="inline-block bg-teal px-6 py-3 text-center font-body text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-white">Learn About Invisalign Insurance</a></div></section></main><footer class="bg-charcoal pt-16 pb-8"><div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6"><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-12 mb-12"><div><div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-24 h-24 bg-teal overflow-hidden mb-5"><img src="/square logo.webp" alt="Elm Ridge Implant and Family Dentistry logo in Killeen, TX" clas